ZH: 这座城市的边界是河流。
EN: The river is the boundary of this city.

ZH: 我们需要在地图上勾画出国家的边界。
EN: We need to draw the country's boundaries on the map.

ZH: 他住在两个国家的边界上。
EN: He lives on the border of two countries.

ZH: 那个小村庄位于山谷的边界。
EN: The small village is located on the edge of the valley.

ZH: 这个房子的后院与邻居的房子之间没有边界。
EN: There is no boundary between the backyard of this house and the neighbor's house.

ZH: 我们必须尊重各国的主权边界。
EN: We must respect the sovereignty boundaries of each country.

ZH: 教师和学生之间应该保持一定的界限和边界。
EN: There should be certain limits and boundaries between teachers and students.

ZH: 他在制定计划时没有超出公司的经营边界。
EN: He did not exceed the business boundaries of the company when formulating the plan.

ZH: 你可以喜欢任何音乐类型，因为音乐没有边界。
EN: You can like any genre of music, as music knows no boundaries.

ZH: 在这个比赛中，创意是唯一的边界。
EN: In this competition, creativity is the only boundary.

ZH: 我们要在地球上的边界尽可能地保护环境。
EN: We should do our best to protect the environment at the boundaries of the earth.

ZH: 家庭应该是孩子们收获爱与安全的边界。
EN: Family should be the boundaries where children receive love and safety.

ZH: 边界不仅仅是一个实际的界限，还是一种文化和价值的体现。
EN: Boundaries are not just physical limits, they also represent culture and values.

ZH: 在相互尊重的前提下，我们可以共享各种观点，没有边界限制。
EN: We can share different perspectives without boundaries, under the premise of mutual respect.

ZH: 边界的设定应该遵守相关法律和法规。
EN: The establishment of boundaries should comply with relevant laws and regulations.

ZH: 当两国领导人沟通达成共识时，边界争端有望解决。
EN: The boundary dispute is expected to be resolved when the leaders of both countries reach a consensus.

ZH: 内政事务是一个主权国家的边界。
EN: Internal affairs are the boundaries of a sovereign country.

ZH: 维护好人与人之间的边界是建立良好关系的基础。
EN: Maintaining boundaries between people is the foundation of building good relationships.

ZH: 边界的划定需要考虑地理因素和历史因素。
EN: The demarcation of boundaries needs to consider geographical and historical factors.

ZH: 儿童需要在父母的边界内成长与发展。
EN: Children need to grow and develop within the boundaries set by their parents.
